Georgian Foreign Investment Rose 24% to $814 Million Last Year

-- B y   H e l e n a   B e d w e l l
-- 
2011-08-15T10:39:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/georgian-foreign-investment-rose-24-to-814-million-last-year.html
Georgian foreign direct investment
rose to $814 million in 2010, an increase of 24 percent from the
previous year, the  National Statistics Office  in Tbilisi said in
an e-mailed statement today.  The revised figure is 47 percent more than a preliminary
estimate of $553 million released in March. The government
expects FDI flows to exceed $1 billion this year after
investment shrank 65 percent in the past two years, Economy
Minister Vera Kobalia said in an interview in June.  The Netherlands, the U.S. and  Turkey  topped the list of the
largest foreign investors investors in 2010, the statistics
office said. Mining, transportation and communications received
the largest amount of capital, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helena Bedwell in Tbilisi at 
 hbedwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
